title: Detecting haemoglobinaemia
text: Serum haemoglobin levels affected altitude individual lives individual’s smoking status. Altitudes 1000 metres increase serum haemoglobin levels. smoker elevated serum haemoglobin levels greater number packs cigarette individual smokes day increases serum haemoglobin levels. recommended serum haemoglobin adjusted accordingly depending altitude individuals lives /individual’s smoking status. recommended adjustment serum haemoglobin based altitude shown table : function get_altitude_correction() provides appropriate haemoglobin correction factor given altitude metres. example, haemoglobin correction factor person lives place 1400 metres sea level determined follows: adjustment -2 g/L measured haemoglobin 1400 metres sea level needed. recommended adjustment serum haemoglobin based smoking status shown table : function get_smoking_correction() provides appropriate haemoglobin correction factor given smoking status. example, haemoglobin correction factor person smokes 1.5 packs day determined follows: adjustment -0.5 g/L measured haemoglobin individual smokes 1.5 packs cigarette per day needed. function correct_hb() provides adjusted haemoglobin values given altitude sea level smoking status. example, individual haemoglobin 105 g/L smoker 1.5 packs day lives 1400 metres sea level adjusted haemoglobin : individual corrected haemoglobin 102.5 g/L.
code: get_altitude_correction(alt = 1400) #> [1] -2 get_smoking_correction(smoke = 1.5) #> [1] -0.5 correct_hb(hb = 105, alt = 1400, smoke = 1.5) #> [1] 102.5

what: Classifying inflammation based on CRP or AGP only
title: Detecting inflammation
text: classification inflammation status based either CRP AGP shown table . function detect_inflammation_crp() classifies c-reactive protein levels based cut-point shown detect inflammation. example, CRP 2 microgram/L, individual classified inflammation. can also set function provide simple integer codes classify inflammation setting label argument FALSE. case, integer code 0 provided indicate inflammation status. useful workflows require/prefer integer codes binary classification. function detect_inflammation_agp() classifies α1-acid-glycoprotein (AGP) levels based cut-point shown detect inflammation. example, AGP 1.5 g/L, individual classified inflammation. can also set function provide simple integer codes classify inflammation setting label argument FALSE. case, integer code 1 provided indicate inflammation status. useful workflows require/prefer integer codes binary classification. functions useful classifying inflammation data one active-phase proteins available.
code: detect_inflammation_crp(crp = 2) #> [1] "no inflammation" detect_inflammation_crp(crp = 2, label = FALSE) #> [1] 0 detect_inflammation_agp(agp = 1.5) #> [1] "inflammation" detect_inflammation_agp(agp = 1.5, label = FALSE) #> [1] 1

what: Classifying inflammation based on both CRP and AGP
title: Detecting inflammation
text: detailed classification inflammation status based combination CRP AGP shown table . function detect_inflammation() accepts values CRP AGP classify inflammation status. example, individual CRP 2 microgram/L AGP 1.5 g/L, individual classified late convalescence. can also set function provide simple integer codes classify inflammation setting label argument FALSE. case, integer code 3 provided indicate late convalescence status. useful workflows require/prefer integer codes classification. detect_inflammation() function can also used assessing inflammation status using one active-phase proteins. title: Detecting iron deficiency

title:
Utilities for Calculating Indicators of Vitamin and Mineral Status of
    Populations
text: micronutr package provides tools determining select vitamin mineral deficiencies using R. Currently, micronutr functions : detecting haemoglobinaemia anaemia based individual’s serum haemoglobin level; detecting inflammation status based c-reactive protein (CRP) alpha(1)-acid-glycoprotein (AGP); detecting iron deficiency status based individual’s serum ferritin level; detecting iodine deficiency status based population’s mean urinary iodine concentration.

title: Correct serum ferritin values — correct_ferritin
code: correct_ferritin(crp = NULL, agp = NULL, ferritin = NULL)

title: Correct serum ferritin values — correct_ferritin
text: crp numeric value numeric vector serum c-reactive protein micrograms per litre (microgram/l). agp numeric value numeric vector serum alpha(1)-acid-glycoprotein micrograms per litre (microgram/l). ferritin numeric value numeric vector serum ferritin micrograms per litre (microgram/l).

title: Correct serum ferritin values — correct_ferritin
text: numeric value numeric vector corrected serum ferritin micrograms per litre (microgram/l).

title: Correct serum ferritin values — correct_ferritin
text: Nicholus Tint Zaw Ernest Guevarra

what: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
text: Correct haemoglobin based altitude /smoking status

title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
code: correct_hb(hb = NULL, alt = NULL, smoke = NULL)

title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
text: hb numeric value numeric vector serum haemoglobin concentration/s grams per litre (g/l) alt Altitude, metres, sea level smoke Simple integer code smoking status classification: 0 = non-smoker; 1 = smoker half packet less 1 packet day; 2 = 1 less 2 packets day; 3 = 2 packets day.

title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
text: numeric value numeric vector corrected serum haemoglobin concentration/s grams per litre (g/l)

title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
text: Ernest Guevarra

title: Correct haemoglobin based on altitude and/or smoking status — correct_hb
code: correct_hb(hb = mnData$hb[1], alt = mnData$altitude[1], smoke = 1) #> [1] 10.2

what: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
title: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
text: set functions identifies haemoglobinaemia specific target groups children 5 years (u5), children 5-11 years age (5to11), children 12-14 years age (12to14), non-pregnant women 15 years (np_women), pregnant women (pregnant), men (men).

title: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
code: detect_anaemia_u5(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia_5to11(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia_12to14(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia_np_women(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia_pregnant(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia_men(hb = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_anaemia(   hb = NULL,   group = c("u5", "5to11", "12to14", "np_women", "pregnant", "men"),   label = TRUE )

title: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
text: hb numeric value numeric vector containing haemoglobin values grams per litre (g/L). label Logical. labels used classify haemoglobinaemia? TRUE (default), status classified "anaemia", "mild anaemia", "moderate anaemia", "severe anaemia". FALSE, simple integer codes returned: 0 anaemia; 1 mild anaemia; 2 moderate anaemia; 3 severe anaemia. group character value specifying population target group identify haemoglobinaemia . Can either one u5, 5to11, 11to14, np_women, pregnant, men. Default u5.

title: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
text: label TRUE, character value character vector haemoglobinaemia status classification (can either "severe anaemia" "moderate anaemia", "mild anaemia", "anaemia"). label FALSE, integer value integer vector haemoglobinaemia status classification (0 = anaemia; 1 = mild anaemia; 2 = moderate anaemia; 3 = severe anaemia)

title: Determine haemoglobinaemia status for various population groups — detect_anaemia_u5
text: Nicholus Tint Zaw Ernest Guevarra

title: Determine inflammation status — detect_inflammation
text: Given laboratory values serum c-reactive protein (CRP) /serum alpha(1)-acid-glycoprotein (AGP), inflammation status subject can determined based cut-values described Namaste, S. M., Rohner, F., Huang, J., Bhushan, N. L., Flores-Ayala, R., Kupka, R., Mei, Z., Rawat, R., Williams, . M., Raiten, D. J., Northrop-Clewes, C. ., & Suchdev, P. S. (2017). Adjusting ferritin concentrations inflammation: Biomarkers Reflecting Inflammation Nutritional Determinants Anemia (BRINDA) project. American journal clinical nutrition, 106(Suppl 1), 359S–371S. https://doi.org/10.3945/ajcn.116.141762

title: Determine inflammation status — detect_inflammation
code: detect_inflammation(crp = NULL, agp = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_inflammation_crp(crp = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_inflammation_agp(agp = NULL, label = TRUE)

title: Determine inflammation status — detect_inflammation
text: crp numeric value numeric vector c-reactive protein (crp) values micrograms per litre (microgram/l). agp numeric value numeric vector alpha(1)-acid-glycoprotein (agp) values micrograms per litre (microgram/l). label Logical. labels used classify inflammation status? TRUE (default), status classified "inflammation" "inflammation" based either CRP AGP status classified "inflammation", "incubation", "early convalescence", "late convalescence" based CRP AGP. FALSE, simple integer codes returned: 0 inflammation 1 inflammation based either CRP AGP; 0 inflammation, 1 incubation, 2 early convalescence, 3 late convalescence.

title: Determine inflammation status — detect_inflammation
text: label TRUE, character value character vector inflammation classification based c-reactive protein (CRP) /alpha(1)-acid-glycoprotein (AGP) values. label FALSE, integer value vector inflammation classification.

title: Determine iron storage status — detect_iron_deficiency_u5
text: Given serum ferritin values, determine iron storage status.

title: Determine iron storage status — detect_iron_deficiency_u5
code: detect_iron_deficiency_u5(ferritin = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_iron_deficiency_5over(ferritin = NULL, label = TRUE)  detect_iron_deficiency(ferritin = NULL, group = c("u5", "5over"), label = TRUE)  detect_iron_deficiency_qualitative(   ferritin = NULL,   inflammation = NULL,   group = c("u5", "5over"),   label = TRUE )

title: Determine iron storage status — detect_iron_deficiency_u5
text: ferritin numeric value numeric vector serum ferritin level micrograms per litre (microgram/L). label Logical. labels used classify iron storage status? TRUE (default), status classified "iron deficiency" "iron deficiency". FALSE, simple integer codes returned: 0 iron deficiency 1 iron deficiency. group character value specifying population target group determine iron status . Can either 5 year old ("u5") 5 years ("5over"). Default "u5". inflammation Logical value vector. subject inflammation ?

title: Determine iron storage status — detect_iron_deficiency_u5
text: label TRUE, character value character vector iron status classification (can either "iron deficiency" "iron deficiency"). label FALSE, integer value integer vector iron status classification (0 = iron deficiency; 1 = iron deficiency)
